<script lang="ts">
  const html: string = "<h1>Calendar Table Row</h1>\n\n<p>A calendar table row represents a single row within a calendar grid, typically corresponding to one week. It wraps day cells or header cells in a horizontal sequence. It is designed to be used inside a CalendarTableHead, CalendarTableBody, or CalendarTableFoot section.</p>\n\n<p>The component renders a <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> element and passes through its children, which are expected to be <code>&lt;td&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;th&gt;</code>, or CalendarTableCell elements.</p>\n\n<h2>Implementation Notes</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Renders as a <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> element for one row in a calendar grid</li>\n<li>Children should be day cells (<code>&lt;td&gt;</code> or CalendarTableCell) or header cells (<code>&lt;th&gt;</code>)</li>\n<li>Designed to be used inside CalendarTableHead, CalendarTableBody, or CalendarTableFoot</li>\n<li>Spreads <code>restProps</code> onto the <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> element for consumer customization</li>\n<li>No internal state -- purely a structural wrapper</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Props</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>children</code>: slot (required) -- cells for this row, typically day numbers or day-of-week labels</li>\n<li><code>...restProps</code>: Any additional HTML attributes passed to the <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> element</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;CalendarTableBody&gt;\n  &lt;CalendarTableRow&gt;\n    &lt;CalendarTableTD&gt;1&lt;/CalendarTableTD&gt;\n    &lt;CalendarTableTD&gt;2&lt;/CalendarTableTD&gt;\n    &lt;CalendarTableTD&gt;3&lt;/CalendarTableTD&gt;\n    &lt;CalendarTableTD&gt;4&lt;/CalendarTableTD&gt;\n    &lt;CalendarTableTD&gt;5&lt;/CalendarTableTD&gt;\n    &lt;CalendarTableTD&gt;6&lt;/CalendarTableTD&gt;\n    &lt;CalendarTableTD&gt;7&lt;/CalendarTableTD&gt;\n  &lt;/CalendarTableRow&gt;\n  &lt;CalendarTableRow&gt;\n    &lt;CalendarTableTD today selected&gt;8&lt;/CalendarTableTD&gt;\n    &lt;CalendarTableTD&gt;9&lt;/CalendarTableTD&gt;\n    &lt;CalendarTableTD&gt;10&lt;/CalendarTableTD&gt;\n    &lt;CalendarTableTD&gt;11&lt;/CalendarTableTD&gt;\n    &lt;CalendarTableTD&gt;12&lt;/CalendarTableTD&gt;\n    &lt;CalendarTableTD&gt;13&lt;/CalendarTableTD&gt;\n    &lt;CalendarTableTD&gt;14&lt;/CalendarTableTD&gt;\n  &lt;/CalendarTableRow&gt;\n&lt;/CalendarTableBody&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Keyboard Interactions</h2>\n\n<p>None -- this component is a passive container. Keyboard navigation is handled by the parent CalendarTable grid.</p>\n\n<h2>ARIA</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Implicit <code>row</code> role from the <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> element -- identifies a row of cells within the grid</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Use inside CalendarTable to provide the <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> for each row of the calendar grid</li>\n<li>Use within CalendarTableHead, CalendarTableBody, or CalendarTableFoot to represent one week or one header row</li>\n<li>Use when you need a row container for CalendarTableTD day cells or <code>&lt;th&gt;</code> header cells</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When Not to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Do not use outside CalendarTable -- use TableRow or DataTableRow for other table types</li>\n<li>Do not use for non-table layouts -- use a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> with flexbox or grid styles instead</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Headless</h2>\n\n<p>This component provides a semantic <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> element with implicit <code>row</code> role and zero visual styling. The consumer is responsible for all CSS including row height, cell alignment, borders between rows, and any alternate-row shading.</p>\n\n<h2>Styles</h2>\n\n<p>The consumer provides all CSS styling. The component renders with a <code>.calendar-table-row</code> class for targeting. No default styles are included — this is a fully headless component.</p>\n\n<h2>Testing</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Verify the component renders a <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> element with class <code>calendar-table-row</code></li>\n<li>Verify pass-through attributes are applied</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Advice</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Designers</strong>: Maintain consistent row heights across all weeks. Use subtle borders or spacing between rows to aid scanning.</li>\n<li><strong>Developers</strong>: Each row in the body should contain exactly 7 cells for a standard weekly view. Use CalendarTableCell for day cells and <code>&lt;th&gt;</code> for header cells.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Composition</h2>\n\n<p>CalendarTableRow is part of the CalendarTable composition pattern:</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>CalendarTable</strong> -- outer <code>&lt;table&gt;</code> with <code>role=\"grid\"</code>.</li>\n<li><strong>CalendarTableHead/Body/Foot</strong> -- section groupings.</li>\n<li><strong>CalendarTableRow</strong> -- <code>&lt;tr&gt;</code> representing one week or header row.</li>\n<li><strong>CalendarTableCell</strong> -- <code>&lt;td&gt;</code> representing one day.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;CalendarTableBody&gt;\n  &lt;CalendarTableRow&gt;\n    &lt;CalendarTableCell&gt;1&lt;/CalendarTableCell&gt;\n    &lt;CalendarTableCell&gt;2&lt;/CalendarTableCell&gt;\n    &lt;CalendarTableCell&gt;3&lt;/CalendarTableCell&gt;\n  &lt;/CalendarTableRow&gt;\n&lt;/CalendarTableBody&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Related components</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>calendar-table</code> — a calendar table interactive grid for managing dates, days, etc. &lt;table&gt;</li>\n<li><code>calendar-table-body</code> — a calendar table interactive grid tbody for managing dates, days, etc. &lt;tbody&gt;</li>\n<li><code>calendar-table-foot</code> — a calendar table interactive grid tfoot for managing dates, days, etc. &lt;tfoot&gt;</li>\n<li><code>calendar-table-head</code> — a calendar table interactive grid thead for managing dates, days, etc. &lt;thead&gt;</li>\n<li><code>calendar-table-td</code> — a calendar table interactive grid data cell for managing dates, days, etc. &lt;td&gt;</li>\n<li><code>calendar-table-th</code> — a calendar table interactive grid header cell for managing dates, days, etc. &lt;th&gt;</li>\n<li><code>table</code> — a table with rows and columns &lt;table&gt;</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>References</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>WAI-ARIA Grid Pattern: https://www.w3.org/WAI/ARIA/apg/patterns/grid/</li>\n</ul>";
</script>

